Toyota (Nigeria) Limited (TNL) was the cynosure of all eyes at annual Nigeria Auto Journalists Association (NAJA) awards held at Eko Hotel in Lagos. The auto firm carted away three awards on the night. Its Chairman Chief Michael Ade.Ojo was also named Pillar of Nigeria Auto Industry, in recognition of his contribution to the industry, spanning over 50 years Toyota Starlet, a new entrant in the company’s array of models, won the Most Transformed New Entrant of the Year award. Toyota Hilux fondly nicknamed the workhorse, won the Pick-Up of the Year award while the Toyota Hiace won the Minibus of the Year award.   Coscharis showcases locally-assembled Renault vehicles     CFAO gets Toyota Forklifts deal     Massilia Motors wins Innovative Company of the Year Award   - Advertisement - The new generation Starlet and Hilux had a few weeks ago been released for a comprehensive test drive at Ilara-Mokin Hill, a race track, located in the hometown of the Chief Ade.Ojo. According to Mrs Bukonla Ogunnusi, Public Relations and Advert Manager at the TNL, the awards were dedicated to customers for their loyalty to the brand and continued patronage. She described TNL as auto industry giant and leader of the various auto brands marketed in Nigeria. “The NAJA Awards was instituted to reward and recognise vehicle models that performed outstandingly well and rose above their peers within the year. Toyota (Nigeria) Limited (TNL) models shone like a million stars at the event winning three of the NAJA prized awards,” Mrs Ogunnusi said. She expressed joy at the performance of the brand, adding, “The awards were dedicated to customers for their loyalty to the brand and continued patronage.”